         <notesStmt>
            <note type="summary">1. Z. did reply to Kohen’s letter. He asked him to come
                            and also extends the invitation to Rovigo so that the three can study
                            Kabbalah together. If Kohen should be prevented from coming by his
                            duties he will answer his questions via letter and through Rovigo. He
                            worries that in their absence from him his students might confuse the
                            kabbalistic teachings of Isaac Luria, Menachem Azarya da Fano, and Moses
                            Cordovero as he has seen many Italian rabbis do. 2. His copyist is
                            working on Sefer Nagid mitsvah for Rovigo and will then commence copying
                            another book for him, provided that Rovigo will return other books. Z.
                            does not want to know about any books by da Fano Rovigo might have, as
                            he does not read his works. Z. has only the one copy of Sefer Shaʿarei
                            Tsion which he gave to Rovigo.</note>
            <note type="incipit" xml:lang="he">ברוך מבנים אש״ר דרכו</note>
